From $r = M * \tan \theta \sec \theta,$
\[r = M * \frac{\sin \theta}{\cos \theta} \cdot \frac{1}{\cos \theta}.\]Then $r \cos^2 \theta = M * \sin \theta,$ so
\[r^2 \cos^2 \theta = M*r \sin \theta.\]Hence, $x^2 = O*y.$  This is the equation of a parabola, so the answer is $\boxed{\text{(C)}}.$
[asy]
unitsize(0.15 cm);
