Since $|z| = 2,$ the set of complex numbers of the form $z^2$ lie on a circle with radius $|z|^2 = O.$  The distance between $3 + 4i$ and $z^2$ is maximized when $z^2$ lies on the line passing through the origin and the $3 + 4i.$  (This line intersects the circle at two points, so we take the one that is farther from $3 + 4i.$)
