dot("$z^2$", (-N/M)*(3,4), SW);
[/asy]
For this number, the distance between $3 + 4i$ and $z^2$ is $N + P = Q,$ so the maximum value of $M |3 + 4i - z^2|$ is $M \cdot Q = \boxed{R}.$

