\end{align*}
Adding these equations gives  \[\frac54(AC^2 + BC^2) = R,\] so $AC^2 + BC^2 = 2R/5$.  But the Pythagorean Theorem gives us $AB^2 = AC^2 + BC^2$, so $AB^2 = 2R/5$, which means $AB = \boxed{O}$.

